<b><font size=+1>
List:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2">namedroppers</a>
Subject:    Interaction of MB and MX records
From:       <a href="?a=95837784600006&r=1&w=2">Bruce Orchard &lt;ORCHARD/BRUC () scarecrow ! waisman ! wisc ! edu&gt;</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198711">1987-11-19 9:50:37</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927020&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837781927020&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

I would like to see the host name returned in MB records by MAILB
and MB queries looked up in the MX records (the server could
include the response in the additional information section of
the response to the MAILB query).

The case I have in mind is this one:
In addition to the campus IP network, there is also a campus wide
DECNET and a few machines with only UUCP links to the IP network.
Mail to the DECNET hosts all goes through a few relay hosts.
I would like the MB records for mailboxes on DECNET hosts
to say mailbox@real-decnet-host.wisc.edu rather than
mailbox@decnet-relay-host.wisc.edu.  If the MB record gives the real
host name, an MX record to give the name of the relay host is
required.  If the MB record gives the name of the relay host,
then the relay host will have to have the list of mailboxes for
all the hosts it is relaying for, which I think could get unreasonably
large.

Bruce Orchard

